  "title" : "Reading Java system properties from command line",
  "body" : "<p>Is there a better way to print system properties from command line? As we can set the property e.g. </p>\n\n<pre><code> java  -D&lt;name&gt;=&lt;value&gt;  //set a system property\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Without writing a class to do that? </p>\n\n<p>If not possible, why is it not possible/feasible/good to do that from the command line ?</p>\n"
}